geneVariantDescriptions.description: KIT D816V lies within the tyrosine kinase domain 2 of the Kit protein (PMID: 19865100). D816V results in constitutive phosphorylation of Kit, activation of Stat5 signaling (PMID: 19865100, PMID: 18390729), induces mastocytosis and tumor formation in mice (PMID: 21148330) and confers resistance to Kit inhibitors (PMID: 22301675, PMID: 19164557).

references.title: KIT kinase mutants show unique mechanisms of drug resistance to imatinib and sunitinib in gastrointestinal stromal tumor patients.
Mast cell hyperplasia, B-cell malignancy, and intestinal inflammation in mice with conditional expression of a constitutively active kit.
Unique effects of KIT D816V in BaF3 cells: induction of cluster formation, histamine synthesis, and early mast cell differentiation antigens.
Pediatric mastocytosis is a clonal disease associated with D816V and other activating c-KIT mutations.
Ponatinib is active against imatinib-resistant mutants of FIP1L1-PDGFRA and KIT, and against FGFR1-derived fusion kinases.
